article.headline: High Point 118, Southeastern 66
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Zione White scored 20 points and added seven assists to help High Point to a 118-66 season-opening win over Southeastern on Saturday. It was the highest point total for the Panthers (1-0) in 36 years, dating to a 121-100 win over Atlantic Christian on Feb. 12, 1969. Chris Meeks added 16 points, Patrick Hilliman had 15, Akeem Scott had 13 and Danny Bathings had 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Panthers, who shot 51 percent from the field and 40 percent from three-point range. The Crusaders (4-3) got 19 points from Johnnie Grant, and 18 points and six assists from Joey Gunter. High Point turned 32 Crusader turnovers into 44 points, and held a 58-35 edge on the boards. The lead changed several times in the opening minutes, and the Crusaders held a 15-11 lead when High Point started a 14-2 run that was capped by Gathings' jumper at the 9:48 mark to give the Panthers a 25-17 advantage. High Point shot 54 percent in the first half and took a 57-36 lead to intermission. After the break, the lead spread as wide as 60 points. A dunk by freshman Arizona Reid gave the Panthers a 101-50 lead with 8 minutes left to play.
